summary: I let my daughter go downstairs to pick out movies to bring upstairs to the Xbox when I'm on my computer.
body:
I let my daughter go downstairs to pick out movies to bring upstairs to the Xbox when I’m on my computer.

Today at went down and I could hear her searching then suddenly “*gasp* Captain America!! Yes! Yes! *suddenly angry type roar* Yeeees!” Then her running as fast as her little legs can carry her, upstairs while laughing kinda crazily.

She found CA:TFA and go crazy excited. Put it in and snuggled down in the bed to watch. Happy as a clam.

Yep. She’s mine. No doubt there. Nerd. ♡♡

blog.description: I'm an old soul, vintage is like my aesthetic. LOVE Marvel. Crazy about music (I'm a sinner P!ATD & loves pop & sweet/sad lovey dovey songs). Drawing is my hobby. Just in general a major weirdo (but ya know I'm a loveable weirdo)

body:
Sweet Beams Ankle Socks [B]

Imagine: When someone meets their soulmate a tattoo/body art of a little bud starts to grow and at the peak of the relationship it will be in full bloom, but with this you don’t only have to have one soulmate in your life time.

Give me credit if you use this pls and tell me so I am able to read it and see the lovely creations made from this little idea.

For example. Girl meets boy fall in love (high school sweet hearts) and later on in life boy or girl gets bad sickness and…dies. Girl or boy is just you know reaaaaaaaaaaaaal sad but carries on and pursues their passion and helps people in their life but doesn’t want to move on (like the mom in HIMYM, btw this idea belongs TM…To Me (tell me if you get it)) but all of a sudden they meet another person and they help them move on and they find another flower growing (these can be growing from any visible spot on the body, legs or arms, etc) and you know they grow old together.

It would also work great with Captain America, for example, he has his first flower bud from Peggy (not fully grown, because they did not have the chance to fully explore a relationship together) and in the modern world he meets someone who’s also lost their soulmate, and they become soulmates and have a family and grow old together or something like that.

I just love this idea, so yeah.

Credit to owner of these awesome tats and photo taker.

title: Time travelling side effects
body:
*The Avengers appear back in time before the fight on Titan*

Tony: Stephen! Peter!

Peter: Hey, where did you all come from?

Dr Strange: So you worked it out? Good. Let’s get on with….. what’s wrong with you all?

Tony: Nothing….just……hang on a minute……*leans over*

Steve: God I feel awful *clutches stomach*

Dr Strange: What…..wait, did you all eat just before time travelling?

Bruce: I told you……..so……..*vomits*

Thor: Can’t travel without a good…..breakfast *throws up violently*

Dr Strange: What is the matter with you? Surely it is obvious to the meanest intelligence that you should not eat for at least an hour before travelling through a time vortex. Even then you should stick to dry food, perhaps a little toast, certainly not……eggs and bacon. Good grief. 

*Thanos appears*

Thanos: Avengers, your destiny is *slips in Bruce’s vomit* eeeurgggh what the hell is this?!

Thor: Thanos! This time I will….just a…..*vomits all over him*

Thanos: Aaaaaaah it’s in my eyes!

*The infinity gauntlet starts to shake, then shatter. Out from it steps a rapidly growing Ant-Man, slightly covered in vomit*

Scott: Surprise, sucker.

Tony: *Still bent over in pain* Peter, web him.

Peter: Yes sir.

Dr Strange: THIS WAS YOUR PLAN?!
